title: Jindabyne - Sightseeing, Dam
content:
For our final day in Jindabyne we were pretty happy to have a quiet one after the hike yesterday.

After some simple morning tea / coffee in town, a few of us went for a drive to check out a dam somewhat nearby. The scenery was nice, and it made for a good way to see something a little different without huge effort.

The rest of the day was mostly just relaxing in the caravan park, enjoying the beautiful day and taking it easy.

The following day we travelled back to Canberra, stopping at the Snowy Hydro Discovery Centre in Cooma on the way. This was very busy, but made a nice coffee and had a great museum / information to walk around and read about the Snowy Hydro electricity system.

And with that, I was dropped at the Canberra airport and the trip was pretty much wrapped up. A nice bit of time away, and a great experience hiking Mt Kosciuszko.
